# Human-testable deliverables

## Principle

If a human cannot run it from the repo and see a clear result, do not ship it as
the primary way to verify behavior.

Prefer **runnable Yarn commands** with visible output over library-only recipes or
documentation-only instructions.

## Do

- Provide runnable entry points: `yarn mirror-init`, `yarn mirror-poll`,
  `yarn mirror-sync`, `yarn mirror-merge`, `yarn test`, and `yarn typecheck`
- Document operational runs in [`docs/usage.md`](../docs/usage.md) and local testing in
  [`docs/run-local.md`](../docs/run-local.md) (copy-paste, run, read `[sync]` / `[PASS]`
  / counts / tables)
- Run the same command yourself before telling the user something works
- Print progress and summary so success is obvious

## Do not

- Do not make importing lib modules the main test path
- Do not split a pipeline into numbered Step01/Step02 scripts or opaque test
  harnesses; use named Yarn scripts that run directly
- Do not write docs that only say "load functions" with no runnable command
- Do not claim verification without running the command in this environment

## Docs

- [`docs/usage.md`](../docs/usage.md): GitHub and local operational commands
- [`docs/mirror-poll.md`](../docs/mirror-poll.md): Block 2 poll and dispatch
- [`docs/mirror-merge.md`](../docs/mirror-merge.md): Block 4 replay and CI
- [`docs/run-local.md`](../docs/run-local.md): local testing and debugging
- [`docs/PLAN.md`](../docs/PLAN.md): design; link to usage.md for run commands

## Agent behavior

- After implementing sync logic, run the relevant command (`yarn mirror-init`,
  `yarn mirror-poll`, `yarn mirror-sync`, `yarn mirror-merge`, `yarn test`, or
  `yarn typecheck`) and report
  actual output (counts, errors)
- Use `--skip-fetch` when mirrors already exist under `.work/mirrors/`
